reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good multivitamins and Iron combination
reviews.reviewText: My iron levels were low the last time I went to the doctor which explains a lot about why I have been tired all the time. I bought these because they come with both iron capsules and vitamin tablets which help the body to absorb the iron. They are non-constipating and they are truly gentle on my stomach. I have had a lot of problems in the past with various iron pills, but these were pretty easy to swallow, even though they didn't taste very good. They had a bit of a maybe vinegary taste to them, but that wasn't a problem if you swallow them right away. Overall, they are a good vitamin and worth the money. I'm happy with them and I think you will be too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The Best Iron Pill - Please get back in Stock!
reviews.reviewText: I've been taking A Active Iron for Women, High Potency Capsules with the 30 Multivitamin pill for a couple of years. The 30 multiviti tablet is included in the box and is a separate pill. It is optional to take, but believe me, take that pink tablet too, because they work well together.I've been anemic for years and I remember it took about a week to start feeling good again. These pills have brought my iron levels up to where they should be and I felt no side effects other than "better". Each pill is individually wrapped for a reason. The iron pill does smell weird when first opened, but has no aftertaste when taken.The iron issues with women like myself, are problematic to say the least, and often lasts a lifetime, give or take ;) I've tried quite a few brands of iron, and this combo works the best - for me.Thank you Active Iron, and Amazon for carrying this brand. I just wish they could keep it in stock. It's made in Ireland so perhaps they are having shipping issues like the rest us.UPDATE - Feb. 1,2022 -
